<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="32" pageNumber="120" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,1398,803,864]" lastBlockId="34.[189,1399,265,467]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="122" pageId="32" pageNumber="120">
This name was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart J." box="[558,762,803,830]" pageId="32" pageNumber="120" pagination="25 - 156" refId="ref20958" refString="Macquart J. 1855. Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. 5 e supplement. Memoires de la Societe (royale) des Sciences, de l'Agriculture et des Arts a Lille 1 (2): 25 - 156. Also published separately as his &quot; Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. Supplement V &quot;: 5 - 136." type="journal article" year="1855">Macquart (1855)</bibRefCitation>
based on a single specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[1182,1340,803,829]" name="South Africa" pageId="32" pageNumber="120">South Africa</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[189,240,838,864]" pageId="32" pageNumber="120">type</typeStatus>
material is lost. 
<bibRefCitation author="Curran C. H." box="[449,622,838,864]" pageId="32" pageNumber="120" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref20173" refString="Curran C. H. 1939. Records and descriptions of African Syrphidae (Diptera). III American Museum Novitates 1025: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1939">Curran (1939)</bibRefCitation>
stated that this can scarcely be a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[1039,1147,838,864]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1147,838,864]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="120">Merodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it is said to have no thorn (lamina) on the metafemur. 
<typeStatus box="[712,771,265,291]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Type</typeStatus>
locality is 
<collectingRegion box="[912,973,265,291]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Cape</collectingRegion>
of Good Hope (
<collectingCountry box="[1178,1239,265,291]" name="South Africa" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">RSA</collectingCountry>
) from where no specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[383,491,300,326]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[383,491,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Merodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected. The description is insufficient, even for an identification to the genus level. In the same publication, 
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart J." box="[686,889,335,362]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" pagination="25 - 156" refId="ref20958" refString="Macquart J. 1855. Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. 5 e supplement. Memoires de la Societe (royale) des Sciences, de l'Agriculture et des Arts a Lille 1 (2): 25 - 156. Also published separately as his &quot; Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. Supplement V &quot;: 5 - 136." type="journal article" year="1855">Macquart (1855)</bibRefCitation>
described one other exotic 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[1224,1332,335,361]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1224,1332,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Merodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from South America, 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1855" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1855" box="[385,870,370,397]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustiventris">
<emphasis box="[385,671,370,396]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Merodon angustiventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart J." box="[679,870,370,397]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" pagination="25 - 156" refId="ref20958" refString="Macquart J. 1855. Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. 5 e supplement. Memoires de la Societe (royale) des Sciences, de l'Agriculture et des Arts a Lille 1 (2): 25 - 156. Also published separately as his &quot; Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. Supplement V &quot;: 5 - 136." type="journal article" year="1855">Macquart, 1855</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which was re-identified as a member of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Knab, 1913" authorityName="Knab" authorityYear="1913" box="[267,549,406,432]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[267,400,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Quichuana</emphasis>
Knab, 1913
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thompson F. C." box="[564,767,406,432]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" pagination="200 - 226" refId="ref22355" refString="Thompson F. C. 1988. Syrphidae (Diptera) described from unknown localities. Journal of the New York Entomological Society 96 (2): 200 - 226." type="journal article" year="1988">Thompson 1988</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, we regard the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1855" box="[1167,1399,406,432]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edentulus">
<emphasis box="[1167,1399,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Merodon edentulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a nomen dubium.
</paragraph>
