<paragraph blockId="34.[188,1400,560,974]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">
A variability in shape of the triangular lamina of the metafemur is present in most of the species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1944" box="[233,495,595,621]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombiformis">
<emphasis box="[233,495,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Merodon bombiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, as seen in figures of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1944" box="[831,1019,595,621]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombiformis">
<emphasis box="[831,1019,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. bombiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1036,1181,595,621]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,843,869]" captionTargetBox="[204,1370,292,785]" captionTargetId="figure-16@33.[189,1398,267,802]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 21.Apical part of male metafemur, lateral view. A–D. Merodon bombiformisHull, 1944 A. Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA2_079). B. Specimen NMSA (FSUNS ID 04276). C. Specimen NMSA (FSUNS ID 04277). D. Specimen NBCN LML-05-5 (FSUNS ID 04282). E. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov., holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). F–G. M. multifasciatus Curran, 1939. F. Specimen NMSA (FSUNS ID 04284). G. Specimen NBCN LML-05-3 (FSUNS ID 03909). H. M. apimina Hull, 1944, paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04086). D, F. Distinct apical dent on triangular process marked with arrow. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013052/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Fig. 21A–D</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[1203,1300,595,621]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1203,1300,595,621]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. lotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1308,1400,596,622]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[198,337,630,656]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,1845,1871]" captionTargetBox="[209,1349,1193,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[189,1398,1169,1808]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 22. Apical part of male metafemur, lateral view. A–C. Merodon lotus Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. Paratypes. A. Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_052). B. Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_060). Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_066). D–F. M. zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. D. Holotype (RMCA; FSUNS ID 25089). E. Paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). F. Paratype (RMCA; FSUNS ID 25090). Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013054/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Fig. 22A–C</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1939" box="[351,554,630,656]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[351,554,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. multifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[568,707,630,656]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,843,869]" captionTargetBox="[204,1370,292,785]" captionTargetId="figure-16@33.[189,1398,267,802]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 21.Apical part of male metafemur, lateral view. A–D. Merodon bombiformisHull, 1944 A. Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA2_079). B. Specimen NMSA (FSUNS ID 04276). C. Specimen NMSA (FSUNS ID 04277). D. Specimen NBCN LML-05-5 (FSUNS ID 04282). E. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov., holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). F–G. M. multifasciatus Curran, 1939. F. Specimen NMSA (FSUNS ID 04284). G. Specimen NBCN LML-05-3 (FSUNS ID 03909). H. M. apimina Hull, 1944, paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04086). D, F. Distinct apical dent on triangular process marked with arrow. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013052/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Fig. 21F–H</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1915" box="[726,852,631,656]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasicus">
<emphasis box="[726,852,631,656]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. nasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[866,1006,630,656]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="34.[189,232,1890,1916]" captionTargetBox="[254,1299,1117,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-300@34.[239,1348,1073,1852]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Fig. 23. Apical part of male metafemur, lateral view. A–B. Merodon nasicus Bezzi, 1915. A. Specimen RBINS (FSUNS ID 29176). B. Specimen TAUI (FSUNS ID 04972). C. M. funestus (Fabricius, 1794) (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F98), dentate apicoventral triangular lamina on metafemur marked with arrow. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013056/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Fig. 23A–B</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[1068,1171,630,656]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zebra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1068,1171,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. zebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1177,1266,631,657]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,1845,1871]" captionTargetBox="[209,1349,1193,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[189,1398,1169,1808]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 22. Apical part of male metafemur, lateral view. A–C. Merodon lotus Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. Paratypes. A. Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_052). B. Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_060). Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_066). D–F. M. zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. D. Holotype (RMCA; FSUNS ID 25089). E. Paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). F. Paratype (RMCA; FSUNS ID 25090). Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013054/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Fig. 22D– F</figureCitation>
). The triangular lamina is more or less dentate, and the apical dens is distinct (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1944" box="[1199,1391,665,691]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombiformis">
<emphasis box="[1199,1391,665,691]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. bombiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1939" box="[189,393,701,727]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[189,393,701,727]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. multifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[407,533,701,726]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[407,533,701,726]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. vittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[540,632,701,727]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) or less distinct, as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[896,992,701,727]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[896,992,701,727]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. lotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[999,1090,701,727]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1915" box="[1147,1274,701,726]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasicus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1274,701,726]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. nasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A scutum with conspicuous pollinose vittae, and terga with pollinose posterior margin and medial fasciae, are characters present in most species, except 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[687,783,771,797]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[687,783,771,797]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. lotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[791,884,772,798]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, characterized by the absence of pollinosity on thorax and abdomen (in females a pair of indistinct pollinose fasciae on tergum 4). Width and shape of vittae and fasciae on scutum and terga vary, especially in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1939" box="[893,1097,841,867]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[893,1097,841,867]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. multifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1915" box="[1111,1238,842,867]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasicus">
<emphasis box="[1111,1238,842,867]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. nasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[1294,1398,841,867]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zebra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1294,1398,841,867]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. zebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,278,877,903]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The colour of the postpronotum, lateral sides of scutum, frons and face in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1939" box="[1136,1339,877,903]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[1136,1339,877,903]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. multifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vary from reddish-brown to black. Specimens from the south of the range (
<collectingCountry box="[1008,1068,912,938]" name="South Africa" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">RSA</collectingCountry>
) are darker than individuals from northern parts (Central Africa).
</paragraph>
